This paper deals with object detection in videos using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised adversarial image-to-image translation, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses datasets related to multimedia (cs.MM) and discusses the application of image translation for cross-domain object detection, which could also fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
